16 (3) Any pawnbroker that knowingly conducts a pawn transaction in violation of
17 paragraph (2) of this subsection shall be subject to a civil penalty of four times the
18 principal amount advanced in such pawn transaction. Such civil penalty shall be
19 recoverable in a civil action brought in any court of competent jurisdiction by the
20 Attorney General or any district attorney."
21 SECTION 2.
22 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
